Crockpot Christmas Candy ❤️💚

Sharing this recipe from last year again, it was such a big hit with family and friends. I’ll be making it again these year to go in goodie baskets.

Ingredients:
1 Stick of Butter
16 ounce Jar of Peanuts
16 ounce Jar of Peanut Butter
1 12 ounce Package of Semi Sweet Chocolate Chips
1 12 ounce Package of Milk Chocolate Chips
1 24 ounce Package of Almond Bark
Crushed up pretzels (Around a Cup)
White Chocolate for drizzle 
Sprinkles

Directions:
•Add butter, peanuts, peanut butter, both bags of chocolate chips and almost bark to crockpot
•Cook on high for an hour stirring every 15 minutes 
•Crush up pretzels and add to crockpot
• Stir all together 
• Using an ice cream scoop, scoop candy on to a cookie sheet lined with parchment paper.
• Let cool/hardened on counter or in refrigerator.
• After hardened, drizzle with melted white chocolate
• Top with sprinkles

It’s Dipsmas Week!

Each day this week I will be sharing a new dip recipe that is perfect for all your holiday get togethers.

First up is this Ricotta Dip with a Roasted Tomato topping. I’ve made this a few times and it’s delicious! This pairs great with crusty bread. I’ve also made it a few times for dinner and paired with a salad, so good. The flavor combinations are perfect! 

Ingredients:

Ricotta Spread:
15 oz Ricotta Cheese
1 Tbsp Minced Garlic
1 tsp Italian seasoning 
1 tsp Red Pepper Flakes
1/2 tsp Parlsey
1/4 tsp Salt & Pepper
Lemon Juice, half of a lemon
1/4 tsp Olive Oil
1/4 Cup Shredded Parmesan Cheese
1/4 Cup Shredded Mozzarella Cheese

Roasted Tomato Topping:
1/2 Pint Grape Tomatoes 
1 Tbsp Minced Garlic
1 tsp Parsley 
Dash of Salt
1/2 Tsp Olive Oil
Grated Parmesan 

Directions:
-Preheat oven to 400
-Rinse and dry tomatoes 
-To a small baking dish, add tomatoes.
-To the same dish add minced garlic, parsley, salt and olive oil.
-Stir all ingredients together and bake for 20 minutes at 400.
-While tomatoes are baking, start on the ricotta spread.
-To a large bowl add ricotta cheese.
- Add minced garlic,lemon juice, seasoning, cheeses and olive oil to the same bowl.
-Stir all ingredients together and add to a baking dish.
-Once tomatoes have cooked, remove from oven.
-Pour tomatoes on top of ricotta spread.
-Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and parsley.
-Bake for 20-25 minutes at 400
-Remove from oven and serve warm with a crusty bread or bagel chips.

It’s Dipsmas Day 3!

Today’s recipe is Crockpot Beer Cheese Dip. It’s my favorite one I’ll be sharing this week. I’m more of a savory person and cheese is my love language, so this is right up my alley!

Ingredient:
8 oz of Mild Cheddar Cheese, shredded 
8 oz Block of Cream Cheese
1/4 tsp Red Pepper Flakes
1/2 tsp Garlic Powder
1/2 tsp Onion Powder
1/2 tsp Paprika
1/2 tsp Salt
1/2 tsp Pepper
2 Tbsp Dijon Mustard
1/2 Cup of Lager Beer
1/4 Cup of Heavy Whipping Cream (forgot to record this portion)
-Green Onion and Bacon Bites for topping.
-Pretzel Bites

Directions:
-Spray Crockpot with nonstick spray
-Shred cheese. You can use a package of shredded cheese, but I think shredding yourself gives this a much better flavor.
-Add cheese to crockpot.
-Add all seasonings to crockpot.
-Add Dijon mustard to crockpot.
-Pour in beer.
-Cook on low for 3 hours.
-Add heavy whipping cream to crockpot and stir.
-Cook for an additional 30 minutes.
-Before serving, add green onion and bacon bits.
-Serve with warm pretzel bites.

Day 4 of Dipsmas Week! 

Today I’m sharing Oreo Dirt Dip. This is a crowd favorite, who doesn’t love Oreos? This is a no fuss rejoice that I love to make ahead of time. Just store in the refrigerator until ready to serve. There are never any leftovers! 

Ingredients:
8oz Cream Cheese, softened
8oz Container of Cool Whip
2 Rows of Oreos, crushed
1 Cup Powdered Sugar
1 tsp Vanilla Extract

Directions:
-To a large bowl, add softened cream cheese.
-Add cool whip to bowl.
-Pour in powder sugar.
-Add vanilla to bowl.
-Using a hand mixer, mix all ingredients together.
-Add crushed Oreos to bowl.
-Use hand mixer again to mix Oreos into the dip.
-Add to serving bowl and top with a few pieces of Oreos
-Serve with fruit, Graham crackers, nilla wafers or more oreos.

Day 3 of Dipsmas Week!

Today’s dip is full of holiday vibes, Cranberry Jalapeño Dip. I love the bright colors and the taste is incredible! Such a fun dish to bring to a Christmas party.

Ingredients:
16 ounces of Cream Cheese, softened. 
12 ounces of Cranberry’s 
2 Jalapeño Peppers, diced
2 Tbsp cilantro, diced
1 Tbsp Lemon Juice
3/4 Cup of Sugar
Dash of Salt

Directions:
-Using a food processor, blend cranberries up.
-In a large bowl add chopped up cranberries, cilantro, jalapeño peppers,sugar, lemon juice and salt.
-Stir all ingredients together until thoroughly combined. 
-Add softened cream cheese to a baking dish and spread evenly.
-Add cranberry topping on top of cream cheese and spread evenly.
-Store overnight in the refrigerator until serving.
-Serve with ritz crackers. 

***You can also make the cranberry topping the night before and combine with the cream cheese before serving. ****

Garlic Ranch Pretzels 🥨🥨🥨

These bite sized treats are packed full of flavor! I love to make these for parties, treat bags or just to have on hand for daily snacks. So yummy.

They go pretty fast so if you have a big crowd, I would double the recipe.

Ingredients:
16 Ounce Bag of Pretzels
1 Ranch Seasoning Packet
1/2 Cup of Olive Oil
1 TSP Garlic Powder
1/2 TSP Dry Dill Weed
1 TSP Grated Parmesan Cheese

Directions:
• Preheat oven to 250 Degrees
• Add Pretzels to a large bowl
• Add ranch seasoning packet to bowl
• Add Parmesan cheese, dry dill weed and garlic powder to bowl
• Top with Olive Oil
• Toss ingredients together until thoroughly combined
• Add to a parchment lined baking sheet
• Bake at 250 degrees for 25 minutes and stirring halfway through 
• Remove from oven and let cool before serving

Crockpot Candied Pecans 

Oh my goodness, these are little bits of heaven. They are crunchy and sweet, such a great combination. I love using the crockpot to make them so I can make a larger batch at one time. Perfect for gift giving. 

Ingredients:
2lbs Pecan Halves
2 Egg Whites
1 Tbsp Vanilla Extract
2 Cups White Sugar
2 Cups Brown Sugar
1 Tbsp Ground Cinnamon
1/4 Tsp Salt
1/4 Cup Water

Directions:
- Add egg whites to a mixing bowl.
- Pour vanilla extract into mixing bowl.
- Whisk ingredients together until frothy. Sit aside.
- To another mixing bowl, add brown sugar, white sugar, cinnamon and salt. Stir until combined.
- To a crockpot, add in pecans.
- Add egg white mixture over pecans. Stir together.
- Add dry mixture to crockpot and stir together.
- Pour in water and stir ingredients together again. 
- Cook on low for three hours, stirring every 30 minutes.
- Once they have cooked, pour onto a parchment lined baking sheet and allow to cool for 30 minutes. (Forgot to film this step)
- Store or bag them up for gifts!

Taco Pinwheels! 

I love making these for “Taco Tuesday”. They are a little different than just the traditional tacos and are a great alternative. They require a few ingredients and minimal work. Win,win!

Ingredients:
1 Pound Ground Beef
1 Taco Seasoning Packet
1 Tbsp Taco Sauce
1 Roll Pillsbury Pizza Dough Classic Crust
1 8 oz package of Shredded Cheese

Toppings:
Lettuce
Tomato
Sour Cream for dipping 

Ingredients:
Preheat oven to 400
Cook ground beef on stovetop.
Drain ground beef and return to pan. Add taco seasoning, water and taco sauce.
Once cooked, remove from heat. 
Roll out pizza dough on a flat surface.
Top with ground beef and cheese. 
Roll dough into a a large size roll.
Cut into 1 inch pieces
Place on a parchment lined/ greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 minutes.
Remove from the oven.
Top with desired toppings and serve!

Doritos Coated Chicken with Nacho Cheese Sauce 

This is one of my husband’s favorite meals, he requests I make it every week, lol. I can’t say I blame him because it’s so good! It’s crunchy, cheesy and packed full of flavor. The Nacho Cheese sauce is delicious and I love to pair it with the chicken and with my roasted broccoli. 

This is a great meal for a weeknight dinner and would also work really well when feeding a big crowd. 

Ingredients:
Nacho Cheese Doritos ( I just added enough to fill my food processor, about 25-30 chips)
1 Pound Chicken Breast (I used thin sliced)
Taco Seasoning Packet
Flour to dredge chicken
Two Eggs
2 TBSP of Butter
2 TBSP of Flour
12 ounce Can of Evaporated Milk
8 ounce Block of Grated Sharp Cheddar Cheese 
Hot Sauce (use as little of as much as you like)
1/4 TSP of Garlic Powder
1/4 TSP Onion Powder
1/4 TSP Cayenne Pepper

Directions:
•Preheat oven to 375
•Crush Doritos in Food Processor
•Prep and clean chicken
•Season chicken on both sides with seasoning packet
•Add flour to a bowl
•Add eggs to a bowl and whisk
•Add Doritos to a bowl
•Dredge chicken through flour, eggs and Doritos 
•Add chicken to a sheet pan lined with foil and sprayed with cooking spray 
•Cook chicken on 375 for 20-22 minutes, flipping halfway through
•While chicken is cooking, start the nacho cheese
•Add butter to a pan and let melt
•Once melted, add flour, garlic powder and onion powder. Stir and let thicken to a roux. 
•Add a few dash of hot sauce and cayenne pepper.
•Add evaporated milk and whisk. Make sure there are no lumps and mixture is smooth.
•Add cheese and whisk until combined. 
•Add more hot sauce if desired.
•Remove Chicken from the oven when cooked through.

Serve immediately.

Crockpot Lava Cake 

This is my niece’s favorite dessert to order out and when I made this version for her a few years ago, she flipped! She requests it for her birthday now! It’s so simple to make and could rival any restaurant version. 

Ingredients:

Cake Base- 
- 1 15.25 ounce Box of Chocolate Cake Mix
- 1/2 Cup Vegetable Oil
- 3 Eggs
- 1 1/4 Cup of Milk

Pudding Portion - 
-  1 3.9 ounce Box of Instant Pudding 
-  2 Cups of Milk
- 1 12 ounce Bag of Semi-Sweet Chocolate Chips

Topping- 
- Vanilla Ice Cream 

Directions:

• Spray crockpot with nonstick spray or use a crockpot liner
• In a large bowl combine cake mix, oil, eggs and and milk and whisk until smooth with a hand mixer.
• Pour cake mixture into crockpot
• In a medium sized bowl, combine pudding mixture and milk. Using a hand mixer, whisk together until it thickens, usually about 2 minutes.
• Add pudding mixture on top of the cake mixture in the crockpot. Do not combine or stir!
• Top with chocolate chips. 
• Cover and cook on high for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. 
• Serve while still warm with vanilla ice cream.

Magnolia Bakery Banana Pudding 🍌

If you are banana pudding fan, this is a must try! My husband said it tasted very similar to Magnolia Bakery’s. It’s a very simple recipe and only requires a few ingredients. Perfect for July 4th!!!

Ingredients:
1 1/2 cup of cold water
One 14 ounce can of sweetened condensed milk
One 3.4 ounce box of Jell-O instant vanilla pudding
3 cups of Heavy Cream
One 11 ounce box of Nilla Wafers
4 Bananas

Directions:
- To a large mixing bowl, use a hand mixer to beat the water and sweetened condensed milk together.
- Add box of vanilla pudding to bowl and beat together until thoroughly combined.
- Refrigerate covered for 4 hours at least, I let mine thicken overnight.
- Beat the heavy cream together in a large mixing bowl. Do this until stiff peaks are formed.
- Fold the pudding and whipped cream together.
- To your serving dish add a layer of pudding, bananas and wafers. Repeat layers once or twice, depending on how large your dish is.
-I like to crush a few wafers and sprinkle over the top.
-Store in refrigerator for at least two hours before serving.

Garlic Ranch Pretzels 🥨🥨🥨

These bite sized treats are packed full of flavor! I love to make these for parties, treat bags or just to have on hand for daily snacks. So yummy.

They go pretty fast so if you have a big crowd, I would double the recipe.

Ingredients:
16 Ounce Bag of Pretzels
1 Ranch Seasoning Packet
1/2 Cup of Olive Oil
1 TSP Garlic Powder
1/2 TSP Dry Dill Weed
1 TSP Grated Parmesan Cheese

Directions:
• Preheat oven to 250 Degrees
• Add Pretzels to a large bowl
• Add ranch seasoning packet to bowl
• Add Parmesan cheese, dry dill weed and garlic powder to bowl
• Top with Olive Oil
• Toss ingredients together until thoroughly combined
• Add to a parchment lined baking sheet
• Bake at 250 degrees for 25 minutes and stirring halfway through 
• Remove from oven and let cool before serving

Garlic Parmesan Ranch Cheez-it’s 

If you are looking for something to make for a party, on a road trip or to watch football, these are it. They are packed with tons of flavor and take no time to come together. My favorite kind of recipe!

Ingredients:
7 oz Box of Cheez-it’s 
1/2 Cup of Olive Oil
1 Ranch Seasoning Packet
1/2 Cup Grated Parmesan Cheese (I use a little extra to sprinkle on top after baking)
1/2 Tbsp of Garlic Powder 
1/2 Tbsp Cajun Seasoning

Directions:
-Preheat oven to 225
-Add cheez-it’s to a large bowl
-To a smaller bowl add olive oil
-Add ranch seasoning, garlic powder, Cajun seasoning and grated Parmesan cheese to oil. 
-Stir to combine
-Add oil mixture to cheez-its and coat evenly 
-Place cheez-it’s on a parchment lined baking sheet. -Make sure to space them out some.
-Cook at 225 for 20 minutes, flipping halfway.
-Remove from oven and top with additional grated Parmesan.
-You can serve immediately, but I like to let them sit overnight to absorb more of the flavor.

Sloppy Joe Slider’s!

My husband is a big fan of Sloppy Joe’s, but I’m not a fan of the canned kind at all! This recipe is the best comprise. He gets all the Sloppy Joe flavor and it’s actually a version I enjoy! 

I love making them into sliders as well. They are loaded with yummy flavor and the melted cheese takes them to the next level! So good!

Ingredients:
@kingshawaiian Slider Buns
4-5 Slices of American Cheese
1 Pound Ground Beef
2 Gloves of Garlic, minced
1 Small Onion, diced
3/4 Cup of Ketchup
1 Tbsp Worcestershire Sauce
2 Tbsp Brown Sugar
1 Tbsp Yellow Mustard
1 Tsp Salt
1 Tsp Pepper

Topping:
1/2 Stick of Butter
Garlic Powder
Italian Seasoning

Directions:
-Preheat to 350
-On the stovetop, place a skillet over medium/high heat.
-Add ground beef, onion and garlic to skillet. Cook until beef is no longer pink and onions are tender.
-Drain fat from ground beef
-To the ground beef add ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, yellow mustard, brown sugar and salt & pepper. Stir to combine all ingredients.
-Let simmer for 5 minutes over low heat.
-Spray a baking dish with nonstick spray.
-Add bottom layer of buns to baking dish.
-Place cheese slices on top of buns 
-Add sloppy Joe mix over cheese.
-Place top layer of buns over mixture.
-In the microwave, melt butter
-Add Italian Seasoning and garlic powder to melted butter.
-Pour over the tops of buns.
-Cover baking dish with foil.
-Bake at 350 for 30 minutes removing foil halfway through. 
-Remove from oven and serve immediately.

Lasagna Soup 🥣

I made this a few times last year, and forgot how good it was! It has all the flavors of a lasagna, but in a soup form! Perfect for a fall night!

Ingredients:
1 Pound Ground Beef or Italian Sausage
1 Yellow Onion
3 Gloves Garlic
2 Tbsp Italian Seasoning
2 Tbsp Parsley
2 Garlic Powder
2 Onion Powder
4 Cups Chicken Stock
1 24 oz Jar Marinara Sauce
1 14.5 oz Can of Diced Tomato 
1/2 Cup of Heavy Whipping Cream
8 Lasagna Noodles, crushed into pieces
1 Cup of Mozzarella Cheese
 
Ricotta Toppings:
1 Cup Ricotta Cheese
Shredded Parmesan Cheese
Shredded Mozzarella Cheese
Italian Seasoning 

Directions:
- Place Dutch oven on stovetop over medium/high heat 
-Add olive Oil to a Dutch oven 
-Add diced onion and minced garlic. Sauté until soft.
-To the Dutch oven, add ground beef.

-Once ground beef has cooked, drain fat. 
-To the ground beef mixture, add tomato paste and stir.
- Pour in Marinara sauce
- Add canned diced tomatoes 
- Pour in chicken stock and stir to combine

- Place lid on top of Dutch oven and let simmer for 15 minutes.
